1
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:33,110
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,509 --> 00:01:36,120
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:45,479 --> 00:01:46,440
You must be mistaken.

4
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,560
Take a closer look.

5
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,720
Man is so delicate—

6
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:49,400
there's no way

7
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,660
she could have done something like this.

8
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:53,960
What's the matter?

9
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,880
Your identity has been exposed—

10
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,200
are you lashing out in shame?

11
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,160
You murderer!

12
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,259
That's not true!

13
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,320
It was not me.

14
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:02,420
It was them who forced me!

15
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:04,330
They forced me!

16
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,620
They forced me...

17
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,979
They forced me...

18
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:12,720
Man,

19
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,570
I know you have your reasons,

20
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,600
right?

21
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,880
Man,

22
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,740
I trust you.

23
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:21,829
Do you trust me?

24
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:26,090
I want to know—

25
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,270
what really happened?

26
00:02:31,170 --> 00:02:32,690
They all deserve to die…

27
00:02:33,370 --> 00:02:35,160
all of them…

28
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:37,650
They all deserve to die!

29
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,720
They all deserve to die!

30
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:44,100
They all deserve to die!

31
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,780
I was never loved as a child.

32
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:52,950
My parents were gone,

33
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,520
my grandfather too—

34
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,750
just me alone.

35
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,980
The other kids always bullied me,

36
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,400
calling me a jinx.

37
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,580
The adults turned a blind eye.

38
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:11,070
Even stealing a bun would get me scolded.

39
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:20,650
Let go of me! Let go!

40
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,160
Struggling won't help,

41
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,680
-Jinx!
-Let go!

42
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,480
Your body's going to be used
sooner or later—

43
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:27,280
so it might as well be by me first.

44
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:40,130
The village women forced me
to work all day,

45
00:03:40,980 --> 00:03:44,590
and at night the men took turns
abusing me.

46
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,340
They didn't even see me as human.

47
00:03:48,370 --> 00:03:50,180
I'd been pent up for days.

48
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:59,280
So I poisoned the well,

49
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:02,490
and killed everyone in the village
with my own hands.

50
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,520
They all deserve to die...

51
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,520
They all deserve to die!

52
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,560
They all deserve to die!

53
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,440
It's them who deserve it!

54
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,840
-They deserve it.
-Don't be afraid.

55
00:05:12,090 --> 00:05:13,050
Yanzhi...

56
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,580
Yanzhi,

57
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:18,050
I just wanted to survive.

58
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,900
They forced me...

59
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:20,750
It's all over now.

60
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,290
It's all over.

61
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:24,250
No one can hurt you anymore.

62
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,280
Tower Master,

63
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:48,400
the bodies of Kou Wan and Zan Hua
have been recovered.

64
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:51,730
Although they committed
capital crimes,

65
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,520
they've been with me for so many years.

66
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,440
Find a secluded spot

67
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:59,580
and give them a proper burial
on my behalf.

68
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,160
Yes.

69
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,600
Wujiu,

70
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,360
how are your injuries?

71
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,360
Thanks to your concern, Tower Master,

72
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,220
my injuries are nothing serious.

73
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,320
Young Master,

74
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,870
I wasn't able
to come farther to meet you.

75
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:22,160
Please forgive me.

76
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,600
No need for formalities.

77
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,800
Having heard so much about Lingya Tower,

78
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,930
I came especially to see it for myself.

79
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:49,000
Welcome to the fourth level
of Lingya Tower.

80
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,000
Making it this far is no small feat—

81
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,070
so I hope you'll cherish it.

82
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,400
Cherish it?
We're not even having an easy time.

83
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,920
-What's there to cherish?
-The first four levels of Lingya Tower

84
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:01,020
are about seeking survival. The next
four levels are about seeking death.

85
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:04,140
The first four are nothing more
than a poetic game.

86
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:07,160
Only if you make it alive
to the fifth level

87
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:10,710
will you understand what it truly means
to be trapped in a hell with no escape—

88
00:07:10,710 --> 00:07:12,440
even death will be out of reach.

89
00:07:12,570 --> 00:07:14,050
So cherish

90
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:17,310
this final survival challenge.

91
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,400
Alright, I've said all that needs saying.

92
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,820
Take care of yourselves.

93
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,480
Those who wish to join this death match

94
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,140
can follow the mute servants.

95
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,570
Those who don't… fine,

96
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,560
you can stay here and slowly wait to die.

97
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,730
You…

98
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,760
Enough talk!

99
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,490
We've all come this far.

100
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,520
Without us,

101
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,560
you might not have even made it here.

102
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,150
Let's go.

103
00:08:06,930 --> 00:08:08,730
Take this letter to the capital.

104
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,120
But I'm the voice-keeper of Level 1…

105
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:13,720
Inside the tower...

106
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,240
You don't need to worry
about what's happening inside the Tower.

107
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,900
I've got it all under control.

108
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,060
What's the matter?

109
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:22,400
Get moving.

110
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:22,880
But I…

111
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,430
Escort her out of the Tower.

112
00:08:42,830 --> 00:08:45,130
I've already sent Wujiu away.

113
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,520
From here on,

114
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,590
do whatever you need to do.

115
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,250
Don't worry, Tower Master.

116
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:54,840
I'll make sure
she suffers more than death.

117
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:08,030
You rarely seem so unsettled.

118
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,580
What's the matter?

119
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:14,200
The Tower Master suddenly sent me
to deliver a letter.

120
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,520
I'm a bit worried.

121
00:09:16,570 --> 00:09:18,930
Are you worried our plan
might be exposed,

122
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:21,380
or about your apprentice's safety?

123
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:26,840
Both.

124
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,240
Don't worry.

125
00:09:28,770 --> 00:09:30,920
I've arranged for someone
to keep an eye on her.

126
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,580
You should be careful as well.

127
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,320
If nothing changes,

128
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,260
everything will proceed as planned.

129
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:39,640
Zhuang Wujiu,

130
00:09:44,570 --> 00:09:46,490
I hope you will
put the greater good first.

131
00:09:46,490 --> 00:09:48,220
[Eternal Prosperity of Lingya Tower]

132
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,280
I'm worried she might be in danger.

133
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,210
Keep an eye on her

134
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,390
until I get back.

135
00:10:09,070 --> 00:10:11,160
[Hall of Elegance]

136
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:14,170
[Floor 4: Hall of Elegance]

137
00:10:17,260 --> 00:10:19,240
This Lingya Tower really knows
how to make things interesting, huh?

138
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,300
First the village,

139
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,230
then the academy,

140
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:22,260
then the caves…

141
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,920
and now the Flower Pavilion.

142
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,380
These paintings are amazing.

143
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:31,850
Could these be the winners?

144
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:35,420
Music, chess, calligraphy, painting…

145
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:37,390
And archery.

146
00:10:40,460 --> 00:10:42,630
[Hall of Elegance]

147
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:43,920
Everyone,

148
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:45,200
thank you for waiting.

149
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,310
[Wan Hongliu, Level 4 Voice-Keeper]

150
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:57,760
I am Wan Hongliu,
the voice-keeper of this level.

151
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:01,880
Welcome to this level's death match—

152
00:11:02,290 --> 00:11:03,740
the Hall of Elegance.

153
00:11:05,110 --> 00:11:06,510
The Hall of Elegance?

154
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,000
What is that?

155
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:08,960
Don't worry.

156
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,600
Let me explain everything.

157
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:13,550
[Hall of Elegance]

158
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,560
Before entering the death match,

159
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,280
you need to choose a team—

160
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,720
blue or red.

161
00:11:28,450 --> 00:11:29,750
No matter what,

162
00:11:29,770 --> 00:11:31,630
we're sticking together, right?

163
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,780
We choose the Red Team.

164
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,050
We also choose the Red Team.

165
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,060
That was fast.

166
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,370
Then only the Blue Team is left.

167
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:41,430
May I ask, President,

168
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:43,310
is there a limit on team size?

169
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:45,000
What if the numbers aren't even?

170
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,400
Lingya Tower never cares

171
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,540
about such minor details.

172
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:50,070
Team selection

173
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,560
is entirely up to you.

174
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:52,910
We choose the Blue Team.

175
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,860
I actually wanted the Blue Team all along.

176
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,180
It doesn't bother me.

177
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:03,120
I'll just follow you guys anyway.

178
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:03,950
Exactly.

179
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:06,910
Just… don't end up opposing that person.

180
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:27,670
Smart move.

181
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,180
You know it—
we're still the ones in charge here.

182
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:38,390
All right, now that the teams are set,

183
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:40,680
let me explain the rules.

184
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:43,320
This match is called
the Hall of Elegance,

185
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,320
so don't expect

186
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:47,920
any crude hand-to-hand fighting.

187
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,770
It consists of three rounds:

188
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,260
first, music and dance;

189
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,960
second, poetry and chess;

190
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,560
third, archery and etiquette.

191
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:57,920
Win two out of three,
and your team prevails.

192
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:02,080
The winners will
all advance to the fifth level.

193
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:04,900
Just dancing or playing chess?

194
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,840
That doesn't sound too difficult.

195
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,420
Yeah,

196
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,760
it doesn't seem as terrifying

197
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,540
as the previous levels.

198
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:11,220
Right.

199
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,500
This is a death match—

200
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,310
you mustn't take it lightly.

201
00:13:15,310 --> 00:13:16,710
Got it, got it.

202
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:19,090
There's one thing I forgot to mention:

203
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,760
this match has a unique twist—

204
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:25,850
I, the voice-keeper, will be
joining the competition personally.

205
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:29,290
The voice-keeper is joining personally?

206
00:13:29,290 --> 00:13:30,640
Then, President Wan,

207
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,360
which team will you be on?

208
00:13:34,020 --> 00:13:36,560
Naturally, I'll be
the captain of the Red Team.

209
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:39,030
Wait, what? That's not fair!

210
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,760
I look forward
to your guidance, everyone.

211
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,480
There's little time—

212
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,290
hurry to the West Courtyard

213
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,660
and reunite with your former teammates.

214
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:09,220
She instructed us to the West Courtyard,

215
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:11,150
but no one's here to show us the way.

216
00:14:12,430 --> 00:14:15,470
This level looks much bigger
than the ones before.

217
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,450
They're trying to be mysterious, huh?

218
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,840
What's this about?

219
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,360
Playing a game with the voice-keeper?

220
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,740
Are we really competing?

221
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,460
Let's not be so pessimistic.

222
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,480
We know each other—

223
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:29,880
we'll be more in sync than they ever are.

224
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:30,600
Yeah,

225
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:31,820
Yanzhi is right.

226
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:33,280
We've been through

227
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:35,640
plenty of storms already on this journey.

228
00:14:36,530 --> 00:14:37,880
Hey, weren't our teammates

229
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,400
supposed to be here

230
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,110
in the West Courtyard?

231
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:43,140
I don't see a single one of them.

232
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,340
Ah! It hurts!

233
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,280
I can't take it…

234
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,500
Captain, you…

235
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,410
I haven't even started the match,

236
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:54,670
and I'm already…

237
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:00,910
Captain!

238
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,080
Captain!

239
00:15:07,890 --> 00:15:10,350
I can't take it…

240
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:12,080
Look up.

241
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,320
Ah…

242
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:15,670
It hurts, Captain!

243
00:15:15,690 --> 00:15:16,460
It hurts so much.

244
00:15:16,460 --> 00:15:17,560
I can't…

245
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:19,110
It's killing me. It really hurts…

246
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:21,170
You won't manage without some force.

247
00:15:21,180 --> 00:15:22,800
You're too tense.

248
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:25,270
How else are we supposed
to get through this?

249
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:26,070
Ahem...

250
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:30,760
You're new here?

251
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:31,780
Yes.

252
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:34,280
Perfect, perfect!

253
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,880
You all look nice,

254
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:38,240
and your bodies are in great shape.

255
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:43,270
Clearly, you can sing and dance.

256
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,760
You're… the captain?

257
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:47,360
Yes,

258
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:48,820
I'm Qi Songyue.

259
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,200
How old are you?

260
00:15:51,230 --> 00:15:52,360
Have you come of age?

261
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,840
Get down and keep going.

262
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:57,670
Mm…

263
00:15:57,690 --> 00:16:00,350
I'm the most musically skilled
among us.

264
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,000
If you are better than me,

265
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,600
the captain can defer to you.

266
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:05,920
We're new here

267
00:16:05,940 --> 00:16:07,520
and obviously not as familiar
with this place.

268
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,920
You should take the lead.

269
00:16:09,230 --> 00:16:10,880
We're all unfortunate souls.

270
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,760
Age doesn't matter.

271
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,400
We just have to look out for each other.

272
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,840
So… what were you just doing?

273
00:16:15,860 --> 00:16:17,680
Oh, you didn't know?

274
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,220
The first round is music and dance.

275
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:21,120
Everyone performs a group dance together.

276
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,080
If anyone makes a mistake along the way
and we end up losing,

277
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:25,520
they will face punishment.

278
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,040
Last time we lost,

279
00:16:27,060 --> 00:16:29,920
the few who were taken
away still haven't returned.

280
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:33,720
Hey, keep pressing down like that.

281
00:16:34,570 --> 00:16:37,490
But President Wan didn't even tell us.

282
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,520
I told you so.

283
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,220
That Master Wan
is the sneakiest of them all.

284
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:41,780
So…

285
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,330
what do we do?

286
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,120
If I don't dance well,

287
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:45,760
won't we…

288
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:46,920
Hey, don't worry.

289
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,540
Look, we're new here—

290
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,890
aren't there a few newcomers
on the other side as well?

291
00:16:50,890 --> 00:16:51,690
Captain,

292
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,960
do you know what they're up to?

293
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,330
Normally, President Wan

294
00:16:55,330 --> 00:16:57,020
and the others practice at the Qunhua Hall
in the East Courtyard.

295
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:59,150
Could you take us to observe, Captain?

296
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,360
As the saying goes, know your enemy.

297
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,080
That way, we won't fall
into chaos ourselves.

